currentDoc:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: Even though audiobooks are a great alternative to reading, there are some significant differences that affect the way I read books.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Even though audiobooks are a great alternative to reading, there are some significant differences that affect the way I read books.

currentSuggestions.original: It's like comparing apples and oranges.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: It's like comparing apples and oranges.

currentSuggestions.original: Reading a book while listening to an audiobook enhances the quality of reading.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Reading a book while listening to an audiobook enhances the quality of reading.

currentSuggestions.original: An audiobook is like watching a movie instead of reading a book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: An audiobook is like watching a movie instead of reading a book.

currentSuggestions.original: But being busy with other things, I've adapted to using audiobooks.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: But being busy with other things, I've adapted to using audiobooks.

ops.insert: An audiobook is like watching a movie instead of reading a book.

currentSuggestions.original: You need a background noise for listening but to read you don't need any background noise at all, which helps you don't lose attention and focus when
currentSuggestions.trimmed: You need a background noise for listening but to read you don't need any background noise at all, which helps you don't lose attention and focus when

currentSuggestions.original: While something is read to me, my mind tends to drift towards thinking about other things.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: While something is read to me, my mind tends to drift towards thinking about other things.

currentSuggestions.original: While listening, you are more often than not letting the narrator tell the story to you word by word without your input or explanation.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: While listening, you are more often than not letting the narrator tell the story to you word by word without your input or explanation.

currentSuggestions.original: Having said this, I do admit there is a time and place for audiobooks.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Having said this, I do admit there is a time and place for audiobooks.

currentSuggestions.original: Reading has a way of helping the reader visualize the scene by oneself, building upon your own thoughts and highlights of the book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Reading has a way of helping the reader visualize the scene by oneself, building upon your own thoughts and highlights of the book.

currentSuggestions.original: Because of how the sentences are written, while you read them, you can answer questions like who is this person?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Because of how the sentences are written, while you read them, you can answer questions like who is this person?

currentSuggestions.original: When you listen to an audiobook your mind tends to wander and the more you drift off the less your mind is sharpened to it.
